[github.com/flutter/flutter](https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/new).

## Steps to Reproduce
If I run Flutter Upgrade I get:

C:\src\flutter\bin\flutter.bat --no-color upgrade
Your flutter checkout has local changes that would be erased by upgrading. If you want to keep these changes, it is recommended that you stash them via "git stash" or else commit the changes to a local branch. If it is okay to remove local changes, then re-run this command with --force.
Process finished with exit code 1

I have no local changes. Or if I do, I don't want them and want to remove them.  Sure I can run with --force but I would sooner fix the problem. For some reason Android Studio wants me to use gradle version 4.10.?? and not the latest. 

_Please tell us what you were doing and what went wrong_

comment_data.body:
This happens (usually because of beta or tip of trunk).  Using the Dev channel should help or using git stash.  if you use git status what files are returned?

```
  (use "git add <file>..." to include in what will be committed)
	android/.uuid
	android/gradle/.uuid
```

See the solutions [https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/18893]( https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/18893)
